158 1. Hi, first of all wanna tell you that it is great pleasure and honor to talk with you, and for the beginning, what is new at Avalon? Ok, well firstly let me say thank you for taking the time to write out these searching questions. Things are always new for Avalon. We have many concerts around Europe this year, we have 3 CD's being released before 2008 and of course we have many friends yet to meet. 2. I saw on few places that new Avalon material could be released soon? Can you tell me something about that like, is it true? How is it sound? Is material recorded? Is there any new in Avalon sound and such things. We have a new CD coming out in September 07 entitled 'The Warriors Call' which in my opinion is the best that Avalon have done. The production os fantastic. We have also just finished recording another CD which will also be released before 08. This CD was meant to be a ballad CD but some of the songs have ended up being really rocking songs. I dont think our band can record ballads hahaha 3. Avalon is on stage for a long time now, many bands appeared and disappeared in a time, a lot of things changed in generally, how do you see scene in the time you released your debut and now? My friend I can give no comparisions to the changes that have been made. Under the old leadership things were stale, stangnent and the 'scene' was full of mistrust. Since the changes Brotherhood 28 goes forward as a positive &amp; 100% united force.As a movement we have reached many new goals and this of course reflects on the bands and its supporters. Of course there are still one or two 'leaders' outside of our movement that needs to cause conflict when they say they work to the same ideals. These are neaderthalls who simply thrive on negative attention while we move positivly forwards. To me there can be no choices! 4. What are the bands that you liked to work the most, I listened to some split CD with White Wash, how did you liked to work with them, and is there plans for similar move with some other band in the future? Also if, what bands would you like to work with? The Whitewash CD was not so good for Avalon. We had a very bad recording and production which I feel also reflected badly on Whitewash. Later this year I have the chance to meet the boys from Whitewash &amp; I will be asking for another split CD with them. I think Whitewash are an awesome band and their way of life way is one to be admired. 5. Musically, Avalon is hard to define, I mean, you can say Avalon is just Rock, HC or something similar, how would you describe your music? Avalon is Avalon. Each CD is different because wh choose them to be.I see no point in playing the same style over &amp; over again. As musicians or songwriters the need to be creative is always there. If I wanted to produce the same style music for every CD then we would have released perhaps 20 CDs rather than the 5 that we have. 6. What bands had the biggest influence on Avalon, and what bands or musicians made biggest influence on you? Of course bands such as Skrewdriver and Brutal Attack inspired me to actually start writing politically motivated songs but my youth was from the time of the original punk rock explosion in the 70's. I guess take a bit of everything and there you have our influence. 7. Beside full length albums Avalon officially released is there any EPs, hidden tracks or something similar that was released or something that is waiting to be released, maybe on some B-sides or something? And since I had troubles to find even these albums, some released material that is hard to find? To tell you the truth I have no idea what music of ours has been released. We record for no profits and any CD's that are given to us we usually give away anyway! 8. What non WP/WN music you like the most? Do you have your favorites in other genres of music? I still listen to punk music especially the underground American scene. I also listen to a lot of metal music and classical music. Guess my tastes have no spectrum haha 9. In the time, I was impressed with song What Happened To Freedom, not only that song was great, but lyrics were fantastic, and what is most sad very truth, at least, bands in my country knows that very well, what is the situation in England, did you ever had problems with your lyrics? Gigs? Problems for Avalon have increased over the years around the world but in England they leave us alone. The fucking German police are total bastards who lick the cocks of the Jews in power. America also seems to have a problem but I still think that underhand forces cause us the initial problem. 10. Situation in Serbia is fucked up, in generally, not only music, our government sucks, people are less and less racially aware, and I fear that number of non-whites is also bigger and bigger day by day, propaganda and fake moral take big influence into peoples lives, what is the situation in England? England is also fucked. Large areas of towns &amp; Cities in England are like walking through parts of Africa or Bangladesh. The youth is totally brainwashed into thinking that the multi-racial experiment is a success &amp; for a young white girl to have a 'Brown Baby' is now fashionalbe. Crime is on the increase and social respect is at an all time low. My girlfriend is a Polish girl &amp; she worries very much for Englands future. She tells me in Poland...no fucking black people haha 11. I remember Avalon got a lot of fans here after the Heritage album, people were delighted with support coming from an English band, in that time, in western media Serbs were the ones that terrorize other people in the region and kill innocent Albanians. How come that you made two songs about my country where did you showed unbelievable support to Serbian people, when no one else didnt even think about something like that? Because I was fucking angry with my government. Many people in England outside of the Nationalist cause were also angry that our Country side with the Jew S.A and involve ourselves in another war that was not our concern. For me, 2 weeks before the bombs started falling I was sitting in Budapest with friends from Serbia drinking beer. 2 weeks later my country is trying to kill them. I will never EVER forgive the British government for this....EVER! 12. Can you tell me what is the influence of ZOG propaganda in England on young people and people in generally? Ok, in simple terms. Advertising is a multi-racial tool they use to the full advantage. On TV and other media's a family life in England shows of 2 parents. One Black, One White and their children a shitty Brown colour. To the young this gives the message that its ok to go outside of your own kind. We also have media promoting Homosexuality and now drug taking. Its now wonder the youth are fucked in the head! 13. How would you describe your ideology, in short? My ideals are simple. Race, Family, Folk 14. Are you religious? No, Religion is a very evil force to me. 15. Avalon is very beautiful name, and also great myth, one of my favorites, do you like other myths, and what are your favorites? Do you like maybe Nordic or Slavic mythologies? Of course Nordic mythology is relevant in 'British' history and is a constant source of inspiration. I read the old stories at every chance and have recently started writing my own fiction based on these. I'm afraid I am very ignorant of Slavic myth. 16. What is by your opinion the biggest problem of the modern society? Lack of respect is a big problem in society. While I reject other races if somebody asked me something in a decent manner then I would probably give them the time for an answer. If somebody speakes to me like a piece of shit then all they get is a hard time 17. What makes you puke? Usually my girlfriends cooking haha 18. Do you drink alcohol, and what is your favorite? I like whiskey. Jack Danials or Jim Beam is what warms my heart. 19. What are the Avalons members favorite football clubs? My team is Newcastle United, Griff is Coventry City, Mark's team is Chelsea and Andy follows Arsenal. 20. Thank you very much for you answers, in the end, do you have some message for your Serbian fans that will read this? Fans?? hahaha. Ok, the words in the song ZOGS NIGHTMARE are still very real today. SERBIA, YOU ARE THE BEACON OF LIGHT. Dont believe the bullshit. 28 till the end

332 Mozda Grci gledaju na Slovene kao na Varvare, ali Grcko-Srbski brotherhood posoji vec 150 godina. Prvi Balkanski, protiv Turaka, ucestvovali su sa nama i Bugari ali nisu nista mogli da osvoje vec su jo i izgubili Jedrene pa se Srbska vojska vracala da ih oslobodi. Posle WWI Bugari nezadovoljni podelom territorija, napadaju Srbiju, Grci dolaze, odlazim, razbijmeo Bugare, uletimo im u drazavu i sve im izlomimo, zato sada Tankistbg tolko mrzi Srbe haha. U prvom svetskom Grci su sakrili nasu vojsku na Krfu i nahranili ih a za uzvrat Srbi su oslobodili Solun i zajedno sa Grcima se vratili u Srbiju u probili Bugarske jedinice. 1991. Grci su ratovali u BiH, zajedno sa dva Ruska odreda, a 1999 sam licno bio u dobrovoljackoj jedinici sa 450 Rusa i 300-injak Grka. Takodje, su bili jedina ne Slovenska zemlja koja je odbila da bombarduje Srniju 99'. Mislim da prijateljstvo lezi u istoj religiji, kao i u ratovima koje smo vodili zajedno protiv Turaka, a Grci jako mrze Turke, tako da sada recimo u Solunu 80% ljudi prica Srbski, a jako puno ih je tamo ostalo posle prvog rata. Ja imam kucu koju je moj pradeda dobio na poklon posle proboja Solunskog fronta. Protiv Makedonaca nemam nista, ali cinjenia je da Filip Varvarin, Alexandar veliki... nisu bili Makedonci vec Grci koji su ziveli u Makedoniji (Thessaleya danasnja), nisu imali veze sa Titovom Makedonijom. Znate me sa SFa, niti sam vredjao Hrvate, niti Makedonce, ja sam objektivan. Nisam vam ja napadao drzavu, vec Srbi iz Krajie, a ja sa njima nista nemam, imam prijatelje u BH Hrvatska, i idemo na Frusku Goru na kampove dosta redovno, a par klinaca internet huligana koja pricaju bajke, i televizijsku istoriju, me uopste ne zanimasju. Civilizivano 88

2297 Hi J, I wasn't sure if it was you or the other girl from the gig. I'm not getting involved - obviously S and S are friends of mine but this is personal business between you which should stay that way. I know the story as I asked when I saw some wicked posts on My Space by a bunch of your friends threatening to cut up S or do her over in one way or another. I'm told that girl got herself involved in all that, in which case she isn't exactly the innocent as claimed. I always make a stance against bullying as I had it myself 20 years ago. Had I not seen those posts on My Space myself I'd have jumped in and stopped S at ISD. (As it happens I wasn't there but I'd have talked her out of it earlier). It's the same reason I object to public gossip - about anyone in our movement whether I know them or not. We all stand by this now as 18 put many staunch activists through hell in the early 90s via rumours and gossip - and still do - which caused a rift right down the middle of things that has never fully healed. The difference between us and them is crystal when you visit both forums (not that I ever visit theirs but have been told.) Theirs is full of shit talking on activists and ours is positive and encouraging. We are committed to drawing those lines. S &amp; S have never slandered you on here or on My Space. Whether they are right or wrong at the end of the day, and I make no judgement call on that as it isn't my place to, public slander is the style of 18 - we pride ourselves on having a lot more class. I know you do things differently in America / Canada but that's why you won't find your name slandered all over the place, not from our camps. It just makes [i:a4d2ed7e98]everyone[/i:a4d2ed7e98] look bad regardless of who's in the right. I hope you understand where I was coming from now. I choose no sides in the debacle but unfortunately people like that girl did choose to get involved. Send my love to L and tell her I miss her! G 828

3104 [b:72219ecfc4]Kona&#269;no sam sloio tekst o mom boravku u Engleskoj.Ako uo&#269;i kakvu gramati&#269;ku greku ispravi slobodno,pa da barem mi nacional-socijalisti ne ispadnemo nepismena stoka?!...i da...zahvale : Maurizio&amp;Varese Skinheads, Cava,Fabio&amp;White Kriminals Bologna Rob,Tony,Kev,and B&amp;H East London [/b:72219ecfc4] [b:72219ecfc4] IAN STUART MEMORIAL 2007-ENGLAND[/b:72219ecfc4] Na put u &quot;zemlju nade i slave&quot; krenuo sam jo u &#269;etvrtak ujutro,sam i pun optimizma,iz pulske zra&#269;ne luke.Dva sata poslije,doavi na londonski Stansted,nakon rutinske kontrole osiguranja i putnih isprava,do&#269;ekao me stari drug s kojim sam se uputio ka lokalnom pubu gdje smo ostali do ve&#269;ernjih sati.Me&#273;utim,kako se sunce polako po&#269;elo sputat,ta od umora ta od velike koli&#269;ine ispijenog alkohola, odlu&#269;io sam ipak oti&#263; odspavat barem na koji sat i tako sam se brzo naao u domu svog engleskog prijatelja.Drugi dan je zapo&#269;eo dosta rano za mene,i budu&#263;i da su tijekom no&#263;i pristigli i ostali drugovi sa kontinenta ,otiao sam zajedno sa njema&#269;kim drugovima(koji su prilikom dolaska u Englesku iznajmili rent-a-car) na doru&#269;ak.Nakon ukusnog i &quot;poja&#269;anog&quot; doru&#269;ka zaputili smo se u sam centar Londona,u posjetu Ratnom muzeju no kako smo se probijali kroz kaoti&#269;ni promet a i kia je po&#269;ela padat pa nam je za prolaz u centar Londona trebalo gotovo dva sata,odlu&#269;ismo ipak nau posjetu muzeju odgodit za koju drugu priliku.U kasnijim popodnevim satima nalazimo se s jednim engleskim drugom koji nas je odveo do samog memoriala koji se ove godine odrao u blizini Northamptona u regiji Midlands.Bina je bila postavljena ispod jednog ogromnog atora,oko kojega posvuda dominiraju pedantno obra&#273;ena polja,panjaci i zelene livade.Prvi dan koncerta bio je namijenjen baladama,tako da su nas akusti&#269;nim gitarama zabavljali mali Stevie(son of skrewdriver) koji je kao i obi&#269;no izveo nekoliko obrada Skrewdrivera,te pri samom kraju ve&#269;eri i legenda nae scene-Ken Mclellan.Sutradan,prvi koji se popeo na stage bio je John iz poznatog kotskog benda Nemesis,te &quot;Last Chance&quot;,dosta dobar RAC bend iz Birminghama koji su u prolosti bili poznati na Oi! sceni imenom &quot;Fatal Impact&quot;.Odmah poslije njih dolazi red na mladi&#263;e iz &quot;Unit 28&quot;,koji su izveli svoj set pjesama u klasi&#269;nom RAC stilu,od kojih su mi u sje&#263;anju ostale &quot;Muslims out&quot; i &quot;White warriors&quot;.Dodao bih da iako ovi mladi lavovi moraju jo proradit na svojim pjesmama,zasigurno su svojim nastupom demantirali glasine kako su na engleskoj sceni danas prisutni isklju&#269;ivi veterani iz 80ih;svaka im &#269;ast,samo tako naprijed! Nakon par ispijenih piva za ankom i uobi&#269;ajenih pozdrava poznatim facama,bacam oko na tandove s propagandnim materijalom na kojima se nudio zbilja irok asortiman robe:od be&#273;eva,zakrpa,kop&#269;a,majica i CDeva do raznoraznih zastava,magazina,postera i portreta.Nije dugo prolo i portugalci &quot;Guarda de Honra&quot; zapo&#269;inju svoju svirku samo ovoga puta s malom promjenom u postavi,naime s njima se na bini naao i Steve ina&#269;e gitarist grupe &quot;White Law&quot;.Priznajem nisam ba paljivo pratio nastup portugalaca kao ni londonskih &quot;Legion of S.George i &quot;Section 88&quot; zbog pojedinih nizozemaca koji su me,istini za volju ,bez ikakvih napora odvukli na ank. Nakon stanke i nakon to smo jo nekoliko puta zaredom &quot;utaili&quot; e&#273;, na pozornicu su se popeli veseli &quot;gusari&quot; iz Avalona.Osim vrlo dobre pjesme &quot;england is my rose&quot;, meni osobno nita naro&#269;ito no jako me obradovala pojava Brada iz Blackouta koji je odpjevao nekoliko popularnih obrada poput &quot;House of Treason&quot;(Skrewdriver) te &quot;Chaos&quot; od 4skinsa.Slijedili su upravo Blackout koji su svojim rocknroll zvukom digli na noge uspavanu publiku,no to je sve bila uvertira u ludilo koje je uslijedilo.Ubrzo instrumente u ruke uzimaju legende iz Brutal Attacka &#269;ime je i po&#269;ela prava predstava.U rekordnom vremenu,Ken je bacio u pravi delirij sve prisutne koji su odgovorili estokim razbacivanjem u pogu.Na moje zadovoljstvo odsvirali su skoro sve svoje hitove sa starijih albuma poput estoke &quot;Return of S.George&quot;,&quot;Let it burn&quot;,&quot;White pride White Passion&quot; zatim i legendarnu &quot;Rock against communism&quot;,&quot;Always near&quot; te ostale.I po tko zna koji put Ken je dokazao svoju sposobnost stvaranja entuzijazma me&#273;u publikom te potvrdio kako i nakon 27 godina postojanja pripadaju pri samom vrhu scene.Uslijedila je kra&#263;a stanka nakon koje su nastupili Benny i momci iz White Law.Odsvirali su sve svoje poznate pjesme poput Fetch the noose,Skinhead heart i Kick the reds in(ina&#269;e moja omiljena).Pri zavretku ve&#269;eri nastupili su jo i ameri&#269;ki Empire Falls te kao posljednji bend ve&#269;eri Blue Max iz Njema&#269;ke.Nakon svirke ostao sam u hali do ranih jutarnjih sati uz hektolitre piva i ugodno &#269;avrljanje sa svojim europskim kameradima.Ukupno je nazo&#269;ilo oko 700 ljudi iz gotovo svakog kutka Europe, a i ire.I iako su trebali nastupit i veterani iz Dublina-Celtic Dawn te velani Celtic warrior,naalost nisu mogli do&#263;.No bez obzira na nedostatke bijae to uspjena i nezaboravna ve&#269;er kojom se navrila 20. godina postojanja naeg bratstva. Slijede&#263;ih dana,zajedno sa grupicom panjolskih kolega,zaputio sam se u razgledavanje Londona,te smo tom prilikom posjetili mnoge pretpoznatljive londonske znamenitosti:Westminstersku pala&#269;u,Big Ben,London Bridge...Naravno nismo mogli zaobi&#263; ni ulicu Carnaby te slavni East End gdje smo posjetili i Upton Park odnosno stadion West Hama. U utorak rano ujutro,nakon to me engleski drug odvezao do zra&#269;ne luke Stansted,ukrcavam se na svoj avion te nakon dva sata ugodnog leta dolazim doma duboko umoran i jo dublje dekintiran,al to je najbitnije zadovoljan.I na kraju zavravam svoj izvjetaj jednim obe&#263;anjem:vidimo se dogodine opet!

6000 Good day comrade, me again. I've recently started up my own blog here in Ulster. So far it's going well, but I have a problem. How do you embed pictures as links? I can install pics &amp; links &amp; youtube etc, but the other is giving me hassle. Any help or advice is appreciated. 14 Words
6001 [quote:6abd9596ec="Dave1973"]Good day comrade, me again. I've recently started up my own blog here in Ulster. So far it's going well, but I have a problem. How do you embed pictures as links? I can install pics &amp; links &amp; youtube etc, but the other is giving me hassle. Any help or advice is appreciated. 14 Words[/quote:6abd9596ec] [color=yellow:6abd9596ec][b:6abd9596ec]Dave, only too glad to help mate. [u:6abd9596ec]LINKING PICTURES[/u:6abd9596ec] To link a picture on a blog page to another URL first you must... Upload the picture. Then highlight the picture usually just by left clicking it once and it will turn a blue-ish colour Above the post you are making there are some icons....click the one that says 'Link' and this will open up a box. Put the WHOLE link in in this box, for example if you wanted to put a picture up of THE COVERT TEAM the link would be http://www.covert-tactics.blogspot.com Then click 'Ok' and when you 'publish' your post, click on the image and the link will now work. We understand that starting out as a 'blogger' can be daunting, especially when you see all the fancy stuff and layouts some folk use. When we first started our blog just over two years ago it was VERY basic but be patient because as time goes on and you quickly learn the ropes you will be doing all that 'fancy stuff' yourself, and taking pride in it. Feel free to ask again if you need any help cos its not a problem and glad we could be of some use to you mate. Heres some good advice.... Try and familiarise yourself with HTML code. If when you look at it you think to yourself &quot;what the fuck, how can I understand that&quot; you'll be right but we can guarantee you that by reading up on HTML and then practicing it you will reap the rewards. Yes it may look boring but you'll be glad you took some time to familiarise yourself with it.[/b:6abd9596ec][/color:6abd9596ec]

We understand that starting out as a 'blogger' can be daunting, especially when you see all the fancy stuff and layouts some folk use. When we first started our blog just over two years ago it was VERY basic but be patient because as time goes on and you quickly learn the ropes you will be doing all that 'fancy stuff' yourself, and taking pride in it. 6263 Oh, ik heb nog een jaar aangesloten bij Nordland sectie als gewoon &quot;lid&quot; (als je het zo kan noemen) maar de fut was er totaal uit en ik zag eigenlijk globaal gezien niet echt het nut meer in van gans de zaak. Optredens zijn ok voor wervingsfondsen maar gans het muziekgedoe en aanhang heeft me zodanig gerriteerd en gedegouteerd dat ik er volledig afstand van neem. Ik denk niet dat we de strijd gaan winnen met x-hondertal dronken lallende skinheads die nadien naar huis gaan en voor de rest gewoon afwachten tot het volgende feestje. Ze zijn niet allemaal zo, dat weet ik wel maar goed. Boeit niet meer. Wat de Vlaamse Beweging betreft vind ik het een zo mogelijk nog grotere hypocriete troep. Wat IS de Vlaamse Beweging eigenlijk nog? Vlaams Belang en satellietorganisatietjes. Alles wat VB niet controleert of kan controleren wordt geboycot en zwart gemaakt, al mag men nog zo vaderlandslievend als Sneysens zijn. Dan gaat men op de Ijzerwake kwelen dat men het Ijzertestament nog altijd levendig houdt. Godsvrede zouden ze nog niet eens herkennen als het hen in de ballen stampte. Innige deelneming voor je opa... Ben je van Italiaanse origine dan of was je opa van hier naar Itali gemigreerd? Wat NSA betreft, ik vind het 1 van de interessantse ondernemingen van de laatste decennia. Het solidarisme is iets wat me persoonlijk al lang genegen is (het VLaamser, kneedbaarder en meer verwezenbaar dan het ronduit achterhaalde Nationaal-Socialisme) en wat verbazingwekkend genoeg VB nooit oprecht in hun programma hebben genomen (tvv hun walgelijk rechts-liberalisme, bah). Wat Eddy Hermy betreft, ik ken de mens al geruime tijd en sprak hem wel sporadisch eens. Hij is 1 van de meer intelligente mensen binnen de Vlaamse Beweging. Ik heb sowieso enorm respect voor hem gezien zijn VMO dagen, ten minste een man van daden, niet louter woorden, net zoals voor al die oud VMO'ers. Dat waren tenminste nog kerels, als je dat vergelijkt met nu.... Ik zou trouwens niet durven zeggen dat Eddy een dictator is, meer iemand met een rotsvaste overtuiging in wat ie gelooft, hij eist van niemand dat men hem volgt.

6271 bedankt voor het medeleven voor mijn opa, ik apprecieer dat. ik ben italo-belg en mijn grootvader is teruggekeerd naar zijn land, nadat de belgische regering hem niet meer kon uitmelken als een koe om voor hen het vuile werk te doen (mijnen). stank voor dank noem ik dat, maar ja... ik vind het positief dat je zo opkomt voor de vlaamse beweging, we moeten daar trots op zijn als vlaming, en ook goed dat je beseft dat die dronkaards met hun 828 eigenlijk zichzelf belachelijk maken en nooit een rol in de politiek kunnen betekenen of serieus overkomen bij de mens op straat. Iedereen maakt fouten in leven, zoals ik er vele heb gemaakt, gelukkig door de geschiedenis goed te leren en te interpreteren heb ik kunnen relativeren en streven naar het correcte, namelijk een fier vlaams volk met zijn eigen identiteit. In de middens van B&amp;H zitten er vol van profiteurs, die de domme leden misbruiken, sorry dat ik het zeg, maar dat komt uit hun eigen mond, en ik moet je geen tekeningetjes maken over wie het gaat....met hun lucratieve merchandising (in Brugge en Kortrijk). ik vind het erg voor de mensen die vlaanderen een serieuze kans willen geven. Wat Hermy betreft, heb ik misschien wat overdreven door hem een dictator te noemen. ik wilde alleen zeggen dat hij toch alles naar hand wilt zetten binnen de NSA, doet hij dat omdat er niet veel capabele mensen aanwezig zijn, dan heeft hij gelijk, maar als ik jou hoor praten en kijk hou jij je teksten opbouwt, weet ik dat hij een grote hulp aan jou heeft. nooit aan gedacht om een forum bij de NSA te starten, omdat ik het hier soms echt redicul vind wat sommigen zeggen. maar dat is mijn gedacht.... surtur, ik ben blij dat ik met jou over het vlaamse gedachtengang serieus kan praten, je kan dat niet met iedereen, zonder dat ze er hitler moeten bijhalen (hij heeft economisch gezien fantastische dingen gerealiseerd en waarden/fierheid terug gebracht bij zijn volk, maar hij was na 1938 een serieuze wakko die ze moesten wegsteken...(wist jij dat zijn generaals dat van plan waren met hem). tot hier deze lezing, sorry voor de dingen die jij misschien niet graag hoort, maar ik vind dat een mens zijn gedacht moet zeggen !!!

6276 Nema problema. Oprosti na gnjavazi. Nadam se da si se dobro proveo za docek nove. Mi smo malo kod mene rostiljali, pili i davili se od puste vrucine. Sto se tice sala Knightsa, izgleda da sam ti uspio nabaviti jednoga. Posalji mi postansku adresu (i potrebne detalje) na kojoj zelis da ti posaljem. Sal je od 2003 - te ima novi grb (Knights) i stari grb (Croatije). Posebno je izdanje za 50-tu godisnjice kluba te godine. Sto se tice ostalog, idem na novu tetovazu u subotu kod glavnog lika B&amp;H Viktorije. Ima svoj studio i daju popust simpatizerima i clanovima B&amp;H. Stavljam grb mog sela (Debeljak kod Zadra), te prezime iznad i natpis &quot;ispod Vrceva&quot; na latinskom ispod grba. Osim toga, pozdrav iz vruceg Melbournea i cujemo se uskoro. Anthony.

6293 Hi Jules I recieved my cookbook and other items this morning so thanks very much and thank vicky for me. 14/88 John
6294 Ja inderdaad, in wezen is gastarbeid een vorm van mensensmokkel (dit verkondigen valt trouwens blijkbaar ook al onder de noemer racisme...). De mensen worden hier uitgebuit en daarna aan hun lot overgelaten. Het verwondert mensen dan nog dat er grote criminaliteit onder allochtonen is. Wat 28 betreft, ik heb geen problemen met de mensen van 28 zelf (toch niet de huidige) maar meer met wat er rondhangt en naar die optredens komt. Mensen kunnen voor mijn part nog 100 jaar &quot;rocken for race and nation&quot; met dat alleen gaat de zaak geen kut vooruit. Ik heb respect voor mensen zoals Stigger, die EN muziek spelen EN tijdens hun optredens mensen proberen motiveren om actief te worden EN naast hun muziek nog politiek bezig zijn en allerhande initiatieven nemen. Groot verschil met zovele anderen die denken dat ze het van het zijn omdat ze in een bandje spelen en veel aandacht krijgen. Ik ben niet ANTI-muziek wel tegen de trend dat sommigen blijkbaar geloven dat alles start en stopt met de muziek. Vroeger had iedere beweging zijn muziekkapel die activiteiten opluisterde. De militanten hadden respect voor de kapel en omgekeerd. Heden ten dage zijn er bijna geen militanten meer, enkel nog honderden muziekkapellen die samen met hun toehoorders dan ook nog eens neerbuigend neerkijken op de weinige militanten. Maar goed, so be it. De dag dat de optredens verboden worden, zal het een ruw ontwaken worden voor velen. Wat dat forum voor NSA betreft, dat ga je tegen Eddy moeten zeggen. Ik weet niet waarom maar jij denkt blijkbaar dat ik ook NSA'er ben.:) Ik kijk wel de kat uit de boom. 8 jaar van mijn leven ingezet voor B&amp;H om dan uiteindelijk enkel maar zeik en gebackstab te krijgen, gaat me geen 2 keer meer overkomen. Het idee zelf trouwens zou ik niet doen, fora zijn in mijn ogen totaal onnuttig. Kijk maar hier, met alle respect voor de mensen die er toch iets pogen van te maken maar echt veel interessante lectuur heb ik hier nog niet teruggevonden (globaal gezien dan, niet enkel Vlaams deel) noch op andere fora. Meestal grossiert het in nietszeggende posts, gezeik op anderen en tegendraads gedrag. Een NSA forum zou denk ik net hetzelfde opleveren. Het verwondert me al dat er nog niet veel tegenkanting geschreven is op de blog berichten. Dat Eddy Hermy de reputatie van dictator heeft zal wel toe te schrijven zijn aan desinformatie vanuit VB hoek. Zoals ik al zei, hij heeft een duidelijk omlijnd gedacht en staat best open voor suggesties maar zoals hij zelf zegt: waarom zou ik rekening houden met de verzuchtingen en kritieken van mensen die zelf toch geen poot gaan uitsteken binnen het concept? En ten dele begrijp ik hem daar wel in (been there, done that).

6303 Heres the link http://www.allnationalist.com/index.htm
6304 ja, je hebt gelijk als je zegt dat je al schoppen hebt gekregen, nadat je 8 jaar je ziel hebt ingelegd. nu kan je er niets meer aan veranderen, je kan er alleen door leren. wat hermy betreft, als hij voelt dat hij niet genoeg steun krijgt, dan is zijn manier van handelen wel normaal, ik zou dan ook zo doen. Waarom denk ik dat je nauw aanleunt bij de NSA....je manier van denken, je struktuur van opstellen lijken soms op die van Hermy (ik bedoel zeker niet copieren !) en je dacht dat ik vandamme was (is hij niet de woordvoerder/pr van de NSA/VJW). als je bent zoals je schrijft, dan ben ik zeker dat je een flamingant bent en niet het typetje dat vele B&amp;H-leden willen spelen. Jij kan dialogeren en je weet over wat je spreekt. Mocht ik totaal verkeerd zijn, dat je niets te maken hebt met de NSA, dan raad ik je aan om er over te denken, want Hermy kan iemand zoals jij goed gebruiken, jij bent een doorzetter en intelligent. Je moet nu niet denken dat ik je botten aan het likken ben, zeker niet, mocht ik je een looser vinden of dwaas, dan zou ik je het ook zeggen, laat dat duidelijk zijn. Wat dat muziek betreft, zijn er altijd winnaars (ik bedoel dan die er alleen aan willen verdienen). Het is zoals overal, zolang er oorlog ergens is, zullen de wapenfabrieken veel geld verdien, is er geen oorlog meer, dan starten ze er zelf n. Het is gemakkelijker om iemand op zijn gezicht te kloppen om hem weg te krijgen, dan argumenten te gebruiken om verbaal te winnen. dus als ik het goed begrijp zal jij niet lang meer moderator zijn van dit forum... nog een vraagje, is dat altijd zo dat er zo geheimzinnig wordt omgegaan als er een activiteit wordt georganiseerd in de streek, ik denk dat er bijna geen volk komt omdat het zo geheim is. Op de site van Bandiera Nera in Italia, staat alles tot in de details op de site. Bang van de politie, die komen het toch altijd te wete. zie de betoging van 21 oktober in brugge. 200 politiemensen, ik dacht dat het FCB-ANderslecht was, zo belachelijk en er is niets gebeurd. Meer openheid zou de mensen meer aantrekken, vind je niet.

6556 Nee, niet echt, vroeger Kastelein maar dat ben ik al een jaar of 2 zo beu als koude pap. Toen ik daar verhuisde ben ik dan ook niet meer geweest. Ik moet sowieso veel weekends werken dus veel tijd om op caf te hangen zit er niet meer in. Ik ga meestal gewoon hier en daar, te zien waar ik afspreek met kameraden. Dat kan in Oostende zijn, Antwerpen of Lier of gewoon hier lokaal. Brugge sowieso al niet veel meer, er is hier gewoon geen kut meer te doen. FCB ga ik nooit zien, voetbal boeit me niet bepaald meer. Ging vroeger soms wel nog eens naar De Platse na de match maar laatste keer dat ik er was hing er daar een ronduit irritante penetrante weedgeur. Metaal verdient inderdaad niet slecht maar een mens moet er dan ook veel voor doen. Niet bepaald het minst vermoeiende beroep (bouw is nog erger jaja) om dan nog te zwijgen van het ploegenwerk en de weekends en feestdagen dus. Ik weet best dat het land bestaat ter wille van de werkende klasse maar gans dat &quot;working class pride&quot; gedoe snap ik niet bepaald. Had ik het geweten had ik toch mijn laatste 2 jaar hogeschool afgewerkt, een luilekker bureaujobke gehad dat evenveel (mss nog meer verdiende dan metaal) en tenminste iedere avond en weekend thuis geweest zodat ik tijd had voor andere dingen.

6572 [quote:41aca8e9e0="d.b.h.b."]Greetings to ya Nicole. How`s things down your way mate? Thanks for the insite and also your congrats. Much appreciated. Mate just writting you this short PM on info regarding the do`s and don`ts on being a moderator.I`m trying to get online a bit more now but work is still keepin` me at bay. Thanks again for your support and hear from ya soon. 828,838 88.[/quote:41aca8e9e0] Hi Reuben, Good to hear from you. Things here are great, Im busy with work and the farm as per usual. Charlie starts big school next year, you are still her favourite Scooby Doo impersonator :lol: . I hope things are going well with you. Are you still living at home or have you bought a place yet? Re your questions.. basically your role as moderator is to keep an eye on posts in the Australian Section and to make sure that if some vigorous discussions/debates start happening that things dont get out of hand. When you moderate you have to very consciously take off your mates hat and stay neutral in things. This can be hard especially in Australia, because it is a small scene and you will know probably 95% of the people posting in there. But your mates should also be big enough to understand that whatever you do it is not personal against them it is just you doing your job as the moderator. They may not like it sometimes, but they should respect it. Just because someone you may not like much posts something that you disagree with, you shouldnt abuse your powers of deletion to remove their posts. As you know, Lilliths abuse of her moderator powers was the number one cause of problems in StormFront DownUnder. Unless a post is deliberately designed to incite disunity, attack or provoke people then let it be, even if it strongly disagrees with what you think, or what the majority of the others think. Just follow your own instinct with it and you will be fine. You are not there to be a censor, everyone is entitled to their opinion, stupid as some of them may be. People can and will argue, people do and will dislike each other thats life. You are not there to try and make the Australian section one big fake happy family. However having said that dont be afraid to make some firm calls. There are some strong personalities in there, and you have to make sure that things stay civil. Unfortunately some people will deliberately say things to bait others. And some people are quick to bite. And others can get overly defensive and go on the attack. Theyre the main triggers you need to look out for. The Patrick OSullivan post is a perfect example. Even if I didnt know who he was I would have banned him. He came straight in and attacked and abused people. That was definitely out of bounds and required action. I actually thought really hard whether to delete his post entirely or to let it stay for everyone to read, as I knew that the consequences of leaving it up could be that some people might get aggro about it, and I wanted to avoid that. However he is a real person in the real world and people have to deal with him in real life, and I thought it was important that people knew what he had said. So in the end I compromised by leaving the post up but with a comment to everyone to try to keep them level headed about it so it didnt end up in a complete shit fight. Also another thing to look out for is airing your dirty laundry in public. The forum is read by antis, and there are also some things should be kept internal within the scene, and within certain organisations. A good example of this (and Im afraid I have to use Ben here ) is a thread that was deleted in the Australian section regarding Volksfront. Yes I definitely know about the tensions between him and Doug, we all do. However Ben posted a message airing how the Hammerskins were unhappy about how the Volksfront chapter was started here. The thread was deleted and rightly so. That sort of stuff needs to stay strictly in-house between Hammerskins and Volksfront. Other people in the scene dont need to know about that, at least not via an internet forum. It does not help the scene at all to air your dirty laundry in public like that. Making judgement calls like that about your mates will be the hardest thing you will face. If there is a particular occasion where it is too close to home and you are not comfortable doing that, just contact one of the admins and we will take care of it. That way they can curse us and not you (haha) Anyway, I hope all of this helps. At the end of the day use your best judgement and you will be fine. If you make a mistake shit happens, dont worry about it and move on. Nobody is going to come down on you because of it. If you are unsure before you take action on anything, please dont hesitate to contact either myself or one of the other admins. We do exactly the same thing between ourselves if we are not sure about something. I am more than happy to give you my view/advice on issues that may arise confidentially and behind the scenes. But it should be you as the Australian moderator that publically comments or takes actions on matters. I know that you will take it very seriously and do a great job! Cheers Nicole :)

6793 [quote:41aca8e9e0="d.b.h.b."]Greetings to ya Nicole. How`s things down your way mate? Thanks for the insite and also your congrats. Much appreciated. Mate just writting you this short PM on info regarding the do`s and don`ts on being a moderator.I`m trying to get online a bit more now but work is still keepin` me at bay. Thanks again for your support and hear from ya soon. 828,838 88.[/quote:41aca8e9e0] Hi Reuben, Good to hear from you. Things here are great, Im busy with work and the farm as per usual. Charlie starts big school next year, you are still her favourite Scooby Doo impersonator :lol: . I hope things are going well with you. Are you still living at home or have you bought a place yet? Re your questions.. basically your role as moderator is to keep an eye on posts in the Australian Section and to make sure that if some vigorous discussions/debates start happening that things dont get out of hand. When you moderate you have to very consciously take off your mates hat and stay neutral in things. This can be hard especially in Australia, because it is a small scene and you will know probably 95% of the people posting in there. But your mates should also be big enough to understand that whatever you do it is not personal against them it is just you doing your job as the moderator. They may not like it sometimes, but they should respect it. Just because someone you may not like much posts something that you disagree with, you shouldnt abuse your powers of deletion to remove their posts. As you know, Lilliths abuse of her moderator powers was the number one cause of problems in StormFront DownUnder. Unless a post is deliberately designed to incite disunity, attack or provoke people then let it be, even if it strongly disagrees with what you think, or what the majority of the others think. Just follow your own instinct with it and you will be fine. You are not there to be a censor, everyone is entitled to their opinion, stupid as some of them may be. People can and will argue, people do and will dislike each other thats life. You are not there to try and make the Australian section one big fake happy family. However having said that dont be afraid to make some firm calls. There are some strong personalities in there, and you have to make sure that things stay civil. Unfortunately some people will deliberately say things to bait others. And some people are quick to bite. And others can get overly defensive and go on the attack. Theyre the main triggers you need to look out for. The Patrick OSullivan post is a perfect example. Even if I didnt know who he was I would have banned him. He came straight in and attacked and abused people. That was definitely out of bounds and required action. I actually thought really hard whether to delete his post entirely or to let it stay for everyone to read, as I knew that the consequences of leaving it up could be that some people might get aggro about it, and I wanted to avoid that. However he is a real person in the real world and people have to deal with him in real life, and I thought it was important that people knew what he had said. So in the end I compromised by leaving the post up but with a comment to everyone to try to keep them level headed about it so it didnt end up in a complete shit fight. Also another thing to look out for is airing your dirty laundry in public. The forum is read by antis, and there are also some things should be kept internal within the scene, and within certain organisations. A good example of this (and Im afraid I have to use Ben here ) is a thread that was deleted in the Australian section regarding Volksfront. Yes I definitely know about the tensions between him and Doug, we all do. However Ben posted a message airing how the Hammerskins were unhappy about how the Volksfront chapter was started here. The thread was deleted and rightly so. That sort of stuff needs to stay strictly in-house between Hammerskins and Volksfront. Other people in the scene dont need to know about that, at least not via an internet forum. It does not help the scene at all to air your dirty laundry in public like that. Making judgement calls like that about your mates will be the hardest thing you will face. If there is a particular occasion where it is too close to home and you are not comfortable doing that, just contact one of the admins and we will take care of it. That way they can curse us and not you (haha) Anyway, I hope all of this helps. At the end of the day use your best judgement and you will be fine. If you make a mistake shit happens, dont worry about it and move on. Nobody is going to come down on you because of it. If you are unsure before you take action on anything, please dont hesitate to contact either myself or one of the other admins. We do exactly the same thing between ourselves if we are not sure about something. I am more than happy to give you my view/advice on issues that may arise confidentially and behind the scenes. But it should be you as the Australian moderator that publically comments or takes actions on matters. I know that you will take it very seriously and do a great job! Cheers Nicole :)

6841 Is een beetje een contradixio in terminis niet? Als Vlaams Nationalist op jezelf gesteld zijn? Tenslotte gaat het Vlaams Nationalisme uit vanuit de volkgeest en het volkgebeuren. En we weten allemaal dat we op onszelf niets aan het systeem gaan veranderen. Ik vond het interview op Rapaille best wel goed. De interviewer was inderdaad wel wat mak en ook voor de hand liggende vragen. Aan de andere kant, dit is een nieuwe beweging dus standaard vragen waren wel op hun plaats. Er zijn afdelingen in West Vlaanderen hoor, in Oostende is 1 actief geworden, in kortrijk en Waregem zouden er blijkbaar binnenkort afdelingen van start gaan en in Brugge is er al 1 actief. Zoals ik al zei, ik kijk de kat nog wat uit de boom maar zal wellicht wel aansluiten. Tenslotte volgens wat ik op de blog lees gaat dat al veel meer uit naar mijn ideologie dan die blinde Hitlerverering en het NS (waar de meesten enkel de oorlog van herinneren en verheerlijken dan nog). Ook begint het niveau me hier zwaar tegen te gaan. De nieuwste poster Little.Hitler (de nicknaam alleen al...) is niet bepaald een hoogvlieger (ook al is ie nog erg jong). Maar bon, de jeugd is de toekomst... En Vandamme is al sinds jaar en dag een kameraad van me en met andere NSA'ers kan ik het ook wel best vinden. Hoe oud ben jij trouwens?

6860 ABSURD - Raubritter - heavy, fast paced, raw-ish but well produced NSBM with skinhead influences. 6 killer tracks. $15 ACROSS THE HUDSON - Our Side Of The Story. USA Street/Oi! very polished sound. AFFRAY Embracing Hatred. Blood Red Eagle RAC side project, improvisation concept. Heavy RAC style with outspoken lyrics. AGGRESSIVE FORCE S/t. one of the best cds to emerge from the USA. Tight, angry upbeat Oi! Punk with WP lyrics. AGNOSTIC FRONT - Fascist Attitudes. High quality bootleg of early material. $10 ANCHORETHOS purification among the dusty stones. Eastern language Viking metal. Well produced. ANGRIFF For Freihiet. Increasing popular Swedish RAC with a harder sound similar to Vit Legion. AVALON Hear The Voice. Recent cd from veteran english RAC group, very nice production. BETTER DEAD THAN RED - Marx Was Wrong. - USA RAC. a mix of Rock and fast-ish upbeat sounds. definately their best album so far. Recommended BDTR/SKULLS split cd Nations of Pride. Better Dead Than Red split with brazil band the Skulls. BLOOD RED EAGLE Burning Down The Churches. New album with bigger/heavier sound and female backing vocals. BLOOD RED EAGLE Australiana Newest CD. Studio outtakes 2002 2004, various styles OI!/Viking/RAC. BOUND FOR GLORY - Requiem. - early and live material from one of the biggest bands in the movement. BRUTAL ATTACK Thunder And Lightning, 25 year cd. All new Material from Ken and the boys. RAC kickin it olskool. CRADLESONG / WHISKEY REBELS split cd Rebelsong. Live cd, good sound quality. USA RAC/HC punk elements. EMPIRE FALLS Show Of Force . USA hardcore, right wing without being uber political, good band for this genre. EMPIRE FALLS On The Attack Same EMPIRE FALLS Scene Of The Crime same EMPIRE FALLS War Is Inevitable Same. EMPIRE FALLS The Underdogs The newest album and the best so far. A superior production, well delivered cd. ENGLISH ROSE / Verszerzodes United Forces Split. Both bands very solid sounding RAC. ENGLISH ROSE Tribute to Skrewdriver. Shit hot tribute to legendary RAC gods Skrewdriver. Really good album. ENGLISH ROSE/ KILL BABY KILL split. One of the best OI!/RAC albums to come out in years IMHO. FINAL WAR Glory Unending. If you havent cottoned onto this yet, where have you been? Killer USA Oi! Punk RAC FINAL WAR We Speak The Truth. 2nd album from kick arse Melodic USA Oi!/Punk band. With strong political message GROUPSKULL - Triste Realite - French language non political oi. HEADCASE - Coming Home - Earlier album for famous Belgium Oi! group. (English Language) INFANTRY - Sambo:First Blood. Comical USA hatecore more the rough punk sound than modern hatecore. Very offensive. JOHNNY REBEL Vol1+2. A massive collection of JRs Klan hits, Country music sound, HILARIOUS lyrics. KILL BABY KILL Give Back The Oi! New Belgian bands first full length. Absolute hammer RAC OI! This is how skinhead music should sound. (English language) KONKWISTA 88 Integral 2007. Big Collection of tracks by this well known French band. From RAC to Rock to rock, 20 tracks which has just about everything they did between 1989 1991. LEDUNG - Loyalty. Mixed style RAC project from ballad to rock, mixed Swedish and English Language. LEGION OF ST GEORGE. Out Of The Rubble Comes Revenge. WP punk/Oi! Band from England, GREAT original sound. Heavier than usual but another classic for the group. MIDGARD - Pro Patria 3. Swedish language ballads with female vocals by Saga. NOSTALGIA - Forever Together - Ukraine ballads project. Foriegn Language. some english text. OEIL POUR OEIL - Nes Pour En Chier - French oi non political. french language. OIDOXIE popular, German RAC, German language. OVALTEENIES - Race And Nation - Demos, live and 7&quot; matrial from one of the first RAC bands ever. British. PATRIOTIC FRONT - Spirit Of A Nation - USA RAC sound, typically usa, if you like that sound you wont be dissapointed! STORMWOLF Belgian metal/RAC band, Raw and well executed stuff. A band that could go places. SRIKEFORCE UK Hang Your Heads In Shame. English Oi! Sounding RAC. A newer release, great item. TEMNOJAR Hyperborean Dylogy NSBM synth music, nice production, Eastern European. TEST A - s/t. tight and well produced German Oi! band. German language. TMF Its A Thugs Life. 1st album and an absolute killer one. The soundtrack of Thuggery if there ever was one. Contains vocalist from English Rose in one of his best perfomances to date. TMF Sex, Thugs &amp; Rock n Roll. TMF are back for seconds. Raw &amp; Violent rock at its best. Absolute Killer. ULTIMO ASALTO - En Peide Guerar - French oi rock, non political. VALHALLAS PATRIOTS Race Over All German VF band, all songs in English. Punkish RAC. WARBOOTS - s/t - French oi rock, non political. WODEN In Search Of Lost Gods. UK Metal with RAC and Odinist lyrics. W.R.E - Feeling The Change - slovakian language RAC. includes some english texts. WULFHERE - Wer Foftet, Der Rofte - Very dark, bleak and raw NSBM. meat and 3 veg of the genre! V/A FINAL WAR / STONEHEADS split cd. Great new material by Final War. The Stoneheads I am not so fussed on. Worth it for the final war though. V/A - Barsarkar - swedish Viking Rock compilation. featuring aussie's own BLOOD RED EAGLE with SOL, MJOLLNER + more V/A - A Mighty Lion's Roar. low price label sampler in cardboard sleeve. some good material. $6, or $3 with two other purchases. V/A - GROM / SUNWHEEL split cd. - NSBM hammer!, Grom are very raw extreme NSBM, Sunwheel are the spitting image of burzum with better production. V/A - ISD Memorial 2004 UKRAINE. Features Molot. Sokyra Peruna, Svarog, Kolovrat. foreign language. V/A - APRAXIA / MOLOT - split cd. same heavy RAC band in two different incarnations, foreign language features english texts. V/A On The Streets - international RAC compilation with unreleased tracks only, featuring Southener, Blue Max, Aufbruch, Weisse Wlfe, Revolution, Brutal Attack, Retaliator (Billy of Celtic Warrior) and Odur. from traditional RAC to metal to mainstream rock. XENOPHOBE The Xenophobe EP. 2 tracks from NZs first RAC project band, Metal laced RAC. DEMO CD $10.

PATRIOTIC FRONT - Spirit Of A Nation - USA RAC sound, typically usa, if you like that sound you wont be dissapointed! STORMWOLF Belgian metal/RAC band, Raw and well executed stuff. A band that could go places. SRIKEFORCE UK Hang Your Heads In Shame. English Oi! Sounding RAC. A newer release, great item. TEMNOJAR Hyperborean Dylogy NSBM synth music, nice production, Eastern European. TEST A - s/t. tight and well produced German Oi! band. German language. TMF Its A Thugs Life. 1st album and an absolute killer one. The soundtrack of Thuggery if there ever was one. Contains vocalist from English Rose in one of his best perfomances to date. TMF Sex, Thugs &amp; Rock n Roll. TMF are back for seconds. Raw &amp; Violent rock at its best. Absolute Killer. ULTIMO ASALTO - En Peide Guerar - French oi rock, non political. VALHALLAS PATRIOTS Race Over All German VF band, all songs in English. Punkish RAC. WARBOOTS - s/t - French oi rock, non political. WODEN In Search Of Lost Gods. UK Metal with RAC and Odinist lyrics. W.R.E - Feeling The Change - slovakian language RAC. includes some english texts. WULFHERE - Wer Foftet, Der Rofte - Very dark, bleak and raw NSBM. meat and 3 veg of the genre! V/A FINAL WAR / STONEHEADS split cd. Great new material by Final War. The Stoneheads I am not so fussed on. Worth it for the final war though. V/A - Barsarkar - swedish Viking Rock compilation. featuring aussie's own BLOOD RED EAGLE with SOL, MJOLLNER + more V/A - A Mighty Lion's Roar. low price label sampler in cardboard sleeve. some good material. $6, or $3 with two other purchases. V/A - GROM / SUNWHEEL split cd. - NSBM hammer!, Grom are very raw extreme NSBM, Sunwheel are the spitting image of burzum with better production. V/A - ISD Memorial 2004 UKRAINE. Features Molot. Sokyra Peruna, Svarog, Kolovrat. foreign language. V/A - APRAXIA / MOLOT - split cd. same heavy RAC band in two different incarnations, foreign language features english texts. V/A On The Streets - international RAC compilation with unreleased tracks only, featuring Southener, Blue Max, Aufbruch, Weisse Wlfe, Revolution, Brutal Attack, Retaliator (Billy of Celtic Warrior) and Odur. from traditional RAC to metal to mainstream rock. XENOPHOBE The Xenophobe EP. 2 tracks from NZs first RAC project band, Metal laced RAC. DEMO CD $10.
6867 Is een beetje een contradixio in terminis niet? Als Vlaams Nationalist op jezelf gesteld zijn? Tenslotte gaat het Vlaams Nationalisme uit vanuit de volkgeest en het volkgebeuren. En we weten allemaal dat we op onszelf niets aan het systeem gaan veranderen. Ik vond het interview op Rapaille best wel goed. De interviewer was inderdaad wel wat mak en ook voor de hand liggende vragen. Aan de andere kant, dit is een nieuwe beweging dus standaard vragen waren wel op hun plaats. Er zijn afdelingen in West Vlaanderen hoor, in Oostende is 1 actief geworden, in kortrijk en Waregem zouden er blijkbaar binnenkort afdelingen van start gaan en in Brugge is er al 1 actief. Zoals ik al zei, ik kijk de kat nog wat uit de boom maar zal wellicht wel aansluiten. Tenslotte volgens wat ik op de blog lees gaat dat al veel meer uit naar mijn ideologie dan die blinde Hitlerverering en het NS (waar de meesten enkel de oorlog van herinneren en verheerlijken dan nog). Ook begint het niveau me hier zwaar tegen te gaan. De nieuwste poster Little.Hitler (de nicknaam alleen al...) is niet bepaald een hoogvlieger (ook al is ie nog erg jong). Maar bon, de jeugd is de toekomst... En Vandamme is al sinds jaar en dag een kameraad van me en met andere NSA'ers kan ik het ook wel best vinden. Hoe oud ben jij trouwens?
